<subSubSection id="C31AF6E6FFEEFFC3B4D7F9F3FB3A441B" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BBFA56DFFEEFFC3B4D7F9F3FE654573" blockId="8.[151,450,1602,1629]" box="[151,450,1602,1629]" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">
<heading id="D0F71201FFEEFFC3B4D7F9F3FE654573" bold="true" box="[151,450,1602,1629]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" reason="1">
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B4D7F9F3FE654573" authority="Schmidt 1862" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,450,1602,1629]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B4D7F9F3FE654573" bold="true" box="[151,450,1602,1629]" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B4D7F9F3FEB74573" bold="true" box="[151,272,1602,1629]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Scopalina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF91D89CFFEEFFC3B557F9F2FE654573" author="Schmidt, O." box="[279,450,1603,1629]" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" refId="ref11625" refString="Schmidt, O. (1862) Die Spongien des adriatischen Meeres. Wilhelm Engelmann, Leipzig, 88 pp." type="book" year="1862">Schmidt 1862</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBFA56DFFEEFFC3B4D7F93AFB3A441B" blockId="8.[151,1437,1675,2026]" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">
Definition: Thinly or thickly encrusting; soft and compressible; few or no ectosomal spicules; spongin abundant, with extensions of spongin manifest as mounds or fibers arising from basal spongin plate; these fibers may branch and merge; choanosomal skeleton of spicules or spicule bundles with proximal ends or entire spicule enclosed in spongin; choanosome may have a grainy appearance. Larvae are elongated, conical; anterior region wider than the posterior zone; completely covered by short cilia. (Modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="EF91D89CFFEEFFC3B73FF8AAFB36441B" author="Blanquer, A. &amp; Uriz, M. - J." box="[895,1169,1819,1845]" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" pagination="489 - 502" refId="ref9181" refString="Blanquer, A. &amp; Uriz, M. - J. (2008) &quot; A posteriori &quot; searching for phenotypic characters to described new cryptic species of sponges revealed by molecular markers (Scopalina: Dictyonellidae). Invertebrate Systematics, 22, 489 - 502. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 07004" type="journal article" year="2008">Blanquer and Uriz 2008</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31AF6E6FFEEFFC2B487F88EFADC43FB" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="362" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBFA56DFFEEFFC3B487F88EFC0E44C7" blockId="8.[151,1437,1675,2026]" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B507F88EFE104477" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[327,439,1855,1881]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B507F88EFE104477" box="[327,439,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Scopalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have abundant spongin, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B758F88EFCD54477" authorityName="Alvarez, van Soest &amp; Rutzler" authorityYear="2002" box="[792,882,1855,1881]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Svenzea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B758F88EFCD54477" box="[792,882,1855,1881]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Svenzea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are described as having limited spongin, primarily at the nodes of a reticulated spicule network. 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B6FFF8D2FCBE4453" authorityName="Alvarez, van Soest &amp; Rutzler" authorityYear="2002" box="[703,793,1891,1917]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Svenzea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B6FFF8D2FCBE4453" box="[703,793,1891,1917]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Svenzea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tend to have shorter spicules, (
<quantity id="4CF80888FFEEFFC3B039F8D2FAA94450" box="[1145,1294,1891,1918]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" unit="mm" value="250.0" valueMax="300.0" valueMin="200.0">200–300 µm</quantity>
), whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B4D7F836FEA0448F" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[151,263,1927,1953]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B4D7F836FEA0448F" box="[151,263,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Scopalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they mostly range from 
<quantity id="4CF80888FFEEFFC3B669F836FD44448C" box="[553,739,1927,1954]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.4" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" unit="mm" value="1200.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="400.0">400 to 2000 µm</quantity>
(though 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B70EF836FC49448F" authorityName="Blanquer &amp; Uriz" authorityYear="2008" box="[846,1006,1927,1953]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B70EF836FC49448F" box="[846,1006,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">S. canariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
averages only 
<quantity id="4CF80888FFEEFFC3B0DEF836FB5B448C" box="[1182,1276,1927,1954]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9899999999999998" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" unit="mm" value="199.0">199 µm</quantity>
). The skeletal architecture of 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B502F81AFE3B44EB" authorityName="Alvarez, van Soest &amp; Rutzler" authorityYear="2002" box="[322,412,1963,1989]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Svenzea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B502F81AFE3B44EB" box="[322,412,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Svenzea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been noted as more like that of the haplosclerida than 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B077F81AFB0044EB" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[1079,1191,1963,1989]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B077F81AFB0044EB" box="[1079,1191,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Scopalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B0F6F81AFAB744EB" authorityName="Alvarez, van Soest &amp; Rutzler" authorityYear="2002" box="[1206,1296,1963,1989]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Svenzea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B0F6F81AFAB744EB" box="[1206,1296,1963,1989]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Svenzea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are massive or thickly encrusting, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEEFFC3B592F87EFDE544C7" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[466,578,1999,2025]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="8" pageNumber="361" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEEFFC3B592F87EFDE544C7" box="[466,578,1999,2025]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="361">Scopalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are thinly to thickly encrusting.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBFA56DFFEFFFC2B487FF26FADC43FB" blockId="9.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEFFFC2B487FF26FEBA439F" authorityName="Hallmann" authorityYear="1914" box="[199,285,151,177]" class="Demospongiae" family="Dictyonellidae" genus="Stylissa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEFFFC2B487FF26FEBA439F" box="[199,285,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Stylissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are erect, flabellate, or lobate, rather than possessing encrusting morphologies seen in 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEFFFC2B0ABFF26FAFC439F" authorityName="Schmidt" authorityYear="1862" box="[1259,1371,151,177]" class="Demospongiae" family="Scopalinidae" genus="Scopalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEFFFC2B0ABFF26FAFC439F" box="[1259,1371,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Scopalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEFFFC2B129FF26FF6443FA" authorityName="Hallmann" authorityYear="1914" class="Demospongiae" family="Dictyonellidae" genus="Stylissa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B974797FFFEFFFC2B129FF26FF6443FA" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="362">Stylissa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are noted as having a skeletal architecture like that of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C00DEEEFFEFFFC2B70EFF0AFC5943FB" box="[846,1022,187,213]" class="Demospongiae" family="Halichondridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Halichondrida" pageId="9" pageNumber="362" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Halichondridae</taxonomicName>
, with many spicules in confusion.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
